accessibility.text: Assume the Money Market starts at equilibrium at 3%
The interest rate will fall to a new equilibrium at 1%
The Fed creates new reserves making money plentiful at 3%
When the Fed buys bonds: Quantitative Easing (QE)
When there are excess liquid balances, money is plentiful and there is pressure for the interest rate to fall
